<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry, General Staff Discuss `Errors' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401163194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1525 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 Jan -- Despite the work that has been 
done by the Russian Ministry of Defense on building the Russian 
armed forces, certain errors have been made in organizing the 
management of the forces, and in personnel and training work. 
Military communications are giving rise to serious complaints, 
and cooperation with local administrations in resolving matters 
concerning the draft has not been properly established in all 
places. 
  This was stated at a working conference of administrative 
bodies of the General Staff and the Defense Ministry held today 
by Russian Defense Minister Army General Pavel Grachev. 
  An ITAR-TASS correspondent was told at the Defense 
Ministry's 
information and press directorate that the main aim of the 
conference was to reveal the ministry's shortcomings and errors 
in time, and to assess them. 
  Among the positive results of the ministry's work since it 
was set up, note was made of the elaboration of plans for the 
development of the armed forces, for their strategic deployment 
and the organization of rear supplies, and the creation of a 
blueprint for a military training system. 
  On conclusion of the conference, Defense Minister Grachev 
stressed that the correct conclusions would be drawn in the 
armed forces and every measure would be taken effectively to 
ensure the security of the state. 

</TEXT>

