<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev Notes Shortcomings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2401165594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 25 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2401165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by the Russian Federation Ministry of Defense </F>
Information and Press Directorate: "Work Analyzed, New Tasks 
Scheduled"] 
  [Text] On 24 January Army General Pavel Grachev, Russian 
Federation minister of defense, held a working conference during 
which the effectiveness of the work of command and control 
organs of the General Staff and Ministry of Defense was analyzed 
in detail. 
  A great deal has been done in the period since the creation 
of the Russian Federation Ministry of Defense. Plans for the 
organizational development of the Armed Forces and their 
strategic deployment have been elaborated, and the relevant 
directives have been sent to the troops and their implementation 
has been organized. A certain amount of experience has been 
built up in recruiting citizens to military service on contract. 
The Armed Forces rear services support has by and large been 
planned and organized quite well amid the complex economic 
conditions in the state. A concept for the military training 
system has been elaborated. 
  At the same time, not everything has gone smoothly in the 
organizational development of the Russian Armed Forces. Certain 
errors have been made in the organization of the command and 
control of the troops and cadre and training work. Military 
communications, which are markedly lagging behind world 
standards in their development, are generating serious 
criticism. Cooperation with local administrations in settling 
questions of the draft to the Armed Forces has not been 
established everywhere in a clear-cut way. There are also other 
shortcomings which primarily require the responsibility and 
professionalism of the military leaders in order to be overcome. 
  The main aim of the conference which has been held, Pavel 
Grachev noted, is to expose our shortcomings and blunders in 
time. To assess them. And find ways of solving problems. The 
correct conclusions will be drawn in the Armed Forces, the 
minister stressed, and all the necessary measures will be 
adopted to ensure the state's security effectively. 
  [Signed] The Russian Federation Ministry of Defense 
Information and Press Directorate 

</TEXT>

