<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gromov: Navy Must Shed More Staff </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401171794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1500 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Feliks Gromov, the commander in chief of the Russian 
Navy, has stated that quantitative cuts in the navy will 
continue in 1994. At the same time, the navy will be modernized 
with improved models of combat vessels. The main aim is to 
create a small but highly efficient navy that would be less of a 
burden for the country from the economic point of view. 
<H5>  Navy Commander on Nuclear Warheads in Baltic Fleet </H5>
  [Editorial Report] Moscow Russian Television Network in 
Russian 2020 GMT on 24 January carries a video report on the 
visit to the Baltic Fleet by Admiral Igor Kasatonov, first 
deputy commander in chief of the Navy. The announcer, G.Sablin, 
says that the combat and tactical training of the crews and 
vessels of the Baltic Fleet deserves the highest evaluation. He 
says that the admiral talked about the timescale for the 
withdrawal of forces of the fleet from Latvia, and he confirmed 
the readiness of the last major unit--a submarine brigade--to 
leave Liepaja by 1 June. 
  Admiral Igor Kasatonov stressed that with the loss of bases 
in the Baltic countries the Russian fleet is not losing its 
might and mobility. Kasatonov says: "If the fleet now has 27 
percent of the nuclear warheads, then it will rise to 42-47 
percent by the year 2000. On 21 December 1993 I had the honor 
of being the senior person from the Ministry of Defense at the 
laying of the keel of a most modern submarine. In addition, the 
keels of some surface vessels were also laid, and some vessels 
were also completed, but, again, the concept of a new fleet, a 
third millenium fleet, which of course has to pass through the 
government, needs to be confirmed." 

</TEXT>

