<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Ships Begin Exercises </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601183594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1704 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2601183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] More than 20 warships of the Black Sea Fleet began 
exercises as scheduled on Wednesday [26 January], a Fleet source 
told INTERFAX. These are intended to coordinate operational 
command at sea and on land and train the newly-arriving recruits. 
  More than 8,000 young sailors were recruited last autumn, 
with 4,500 of them swearing allegiance to Ukraine. 
  However, the source does not link the current maneuvers to 
Ukraine's command post exercises. 

