<H3> <TI>   Comments on Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701051694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0400 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2701051694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS special correspondents Grigoriy Arslanov, </F>
Vyacheslav Tomilin, Georgiy Shmelev] 
  [Text] Beijing, 27 Jan -- Relations with China are a 
priority trend in Russia's foreign policy, as was stated during 
the visit of Russian President Boris Yeltsin to the PRC in 
December 1992, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev stressed. 
He was speaking before the start of the Russian-Chinese talks 
with a large number of people attending the Diaoyutai residence 
for guests of honor in Beijing. 
  "We should like to raise Russian-Chinese relations to a 
qualitatively new level -- one of constructive partnership -- 
both in bilateral ties as well as from a regional and an 
international point of view," Andrey Kozyrev said. 
  Greeting the Russian minister, Qian Qichen, deputy prime 
minister of the State Council, PRC minister of foreign affairs, 
noted "according to the Chinese proverb 'spring is a wise time' 
and starting something in the spring means it will be 
successful." He expressed the conviction that relations between 
China and Russia would continue to develop in the interests of 
the two countries in the new year. 
  Qian Qichen congratulated Andrey Kozyrev on his being 
confirmed head of the Russian foreign political department. 

</TEXT>

