<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin To Visit Moscow </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701055994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0450 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2701055994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS correspondents Grigoriy Arslanov, Vyacheslav </F>
Tomilin, Georgiy Shmelev] 
  [Text] Beijing, 27 Jan -- In all probability the visit of 
PRC President Jiang Zemin to Moscow will take place in the third 
quarter of this year. As reported today by Galina Sidorova, 
political aide to the Russian foreign minister at the end of the 
first round of Russian-Chinese talks today, the second 
Russian-Chinese summit will be preceded by a trip by Viktor 
Chernomyrdin, head of the Russian Government, to Beijing, as 
well as by a trip to Moscow by PRC Foreign Minister Qian Qichen. 
  Russian President Boris Yeltsin made an official visit to 
Beijing in December 1992. His visit ended the process of 
complete normalization of relations between the two countries, 
having opened up extensive possibilities for the establishment 
of new, good-neighborly and friendly contacts. 

</TEXT>

