<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Leaves for Italy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701071294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0656 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 27 TASS -- Russian Premier Viktor 
Chernomyrdin departed for Italy this morning for a two-day 
official visit. 
  According to the visit programme, Chernomyrdin will meet 
President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro and Premier Carlo Azeglio Ciampi. 
It is expected that the Russian premier will be received by 
Pope John Paul II and will have meetings with members of the 
Italian business community. 
  At the Russian-Italian talks, the sides plan to discuss the 
entire range of bilateral relations, implementation of earlier 
understandings between the two countries, Russia-Italian 
partnership in international relations, the formation of new 
mechanisms for a pan-European system of security and cooperation 
through fuller use of the potential of the Conference on 
Security and Cooperation in Europe. 
  It is expected that the intergovernment talks will result in 
signing a statement by the two governments, an intergovernment 
agreement on the status of burial places of Russian servicemen 
and civilians in Italy and Italian servicemen in Russia, who 
died during the Second World War as well as a memorandum of 
intent concerning an agreement on encouragement and protection 
of capital investments. 

</TEXT>

