<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Details </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2601163394 Yerevan Radio Yerevan in Azeri 1430 GMT 26 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2601163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Radio Yerevan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation in the areas of confrontation in the 
Nagorno-Karabakh Republic [NKR] remains tense. The NKR Military 
Information Service has revealed that Azerbaijan's military 
forces renewed their attacks against the central areas in 
Mardakertskiy Rayon yesterday morning. But the NKR defense 
units obstructed the attacks and inflicted many casualties on 
the enemy. According to reports received by 1030 yesterday, one 
Azerbaijani armored vehicle was hit. 
  Meanwhile, combat operations also took place in the 
northeast 
of the front line. Azerbaijan's military forces tried to 
penetrate the inner areas of Mardakertskiy and Kelbadzharskiy 
Rayons. The NKR forces stopped them. The clashes elsewhere on 
the front line took the form of positional fighting. 
Azerbaijan's aircraft tried to violate NKR airspace yesterday. 
  The NKR freedom fighters hit six enemy armored vehicles in 
the clashes in Mardakertskiy Rayon last night and destroyed two 
of them. The enemy units left the bodies of their dead 
colleagues and fled the battlefield. 
  The NKR Defense Headquarters has revealed that frequent 
clashes have recently been taking place between the Azerbaijani 
military forces and the Azerbaijani People's Front's armed 
groups. 

</TEXT>

