Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Liliya Kuznetsova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 26 January -- A meeting took place today 
between Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Ella Pamfilova, 
minister of social protection of the population. 
  The president's conversation with the minister was connected 
with her recent statement that she refused to enter the new 
government. 
  The minister's office stated that Ella Pamfilova's 
resignation had not yet been accepted and officially she is on 
leave. As for the meeting that has taken place, the 
participants did not reach agreement on conditions for Ella 
Pamfilova to enter the restructured government. 

