<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Constitutional Court Judge Zorkin Resumes Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601225494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1900 GMT 
26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601225494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It has already been reported that Valeriy Zorkin has 
resumed his duties as a Constitutional Court judge. Yelena 
Sandomirskaya reports: 
  [Sandomirskaya] According to Valeriy Dmitriyevich himself, 
he 
did not stop his work in the Constitutional Court, as he regards 
the decision on his forcible removal as unjust and legally 
incorrect, which is, I would like to note, not the same thing. 
But all this is in the past. Today Judge Valeriy Zorkin has 
new problems: to draw up a draft law on the Constitutional 
Court and to elect its chairman. As to the new Russian 
constitution, Valeriy Zorkin said that he has always criticized 
it. But because it is considered to have been adopted, there is 
nothing else to do but to protect the new main law. Valeriy 
Zorkin said that being a judge who always respects the law, he 
will guard any other constitution. I hope that the defense 
process will be held within the court and not far outside its 
framework -- this is what Judge Valeriy Zorkin promised. 

</TEXT>

