<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Release Book on 1991 Events </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601135994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1306 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2601135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 25 TASS -- Boris Yeltsin puts 
finishing touches to a book which is to be published in France 
in April this year, Viktor Ilyushin, top aide of the Russian 
president, told ITAR-TASS on Wednesday. 
  "The main section of the book deals with the president's 
comprehension of the 1991 events when Yeltsin assumed office. 
The author sets out his point of view on the political 
processes evolving in Russia since then, and shares with future 
readers his keen feeling for the country's future", Ilyushin 
said. 
  The book which has about 500 pages has no working title yet. 
"No one has read the book so far," Ilyushin said, adding that he 
does not know who helped the president prepare the manuscript 
for publication. 
  Asked whether people in Russia will be able to read the 
president's reminiscences, the aide answered in the affirmative. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

