<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Shaposhnikov Appointment to Arms Company </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601183094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1748 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2601183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 26 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin appointed Yevgeniy Shaposhnikov, former CIS Armed Forces 
commander, his representative in the state company for arms 
exports-imports, Rosvooruzheniye. 
  The company was set up on November 25 1993 to handle arms 
exports-imports, including weapons, military hardware, 
equipment, double-purpose technologies and strategic raw 
materials. Additionally, it uses its own funds and borrowed 
means to invest in the defence industry. The company has been 
established to protect Russia's state interests while 
determining contract prices for arms exports and control hard 
currency revenues from such deals. 
  Rosvooruzheniye plans to set up maintenance bases and 
training centers for specialists to transfer relations with 
partners purchasing Russian arms and military hardware on a 
long-term basis. The company has been allowed to set up branches 
and offices inside and outside of Russia, including with the 
participation of foreign capital. At present it has branches in 
38 countries and cooperates with 60 countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

