<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Military Review" rubric] </F>
  [Text] The Russian Federation minister of defense has 
issued a directive on re-forming the former Main 
Military-Political Directorate, and over 150 officers and 
generals will have to look for a new job. There will now be no 
more deputy commanders specifically for educational work above 
corps and division level. This work has been given to deputy 
commanders. The sorest point in the Russian Army -- discipline 
-- will be the concern of chiefs of organs for troops' 
conditions and service. 

