<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Minister Arrives in U.S. To Discuss Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2601141594 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0600 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2601141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In accordance with the agreement of Ukrainian 
President Leonid Kravchuk and U.S. President Bill Clinton, a 
Ukrainian Government delegation led by Economic Minister Roman 
Shpek has arrived in Washington. The delegation also includes 
Viktor Yushchenko, Ukrainian National Bank chairman, several 
deputy ministers, and a group of leading Ukrainian experts. The 
delegation was met at the airport by Oleh Bilorus, Ukrainian 
ambassador to the United States, and embassy officials. The 
delegation is scheduled to hold negotiations on a wide range of 
issues connected with bilateral economic cooperation. U.S. aid 
intended for stabilization, restoration, and radical reform of 
the Ukrainian economy based on the market principles will be 
central to the negotiations. The Ukrainian and U.S. delegations 
held a plenary meeting at the U.S. State Department where they 
discussed principles and priorities of economic cooperation 
between the two countries. The Ukrainian delegation also visited 
the U.S. Department of Agriculture where it met with Secretary 
of Agriculture Michael Espy. Members of the Ukrainian delegation 
met with executives from the Foreign Private Investment 
Corporation and the U.S. Trade Development Agency. 

</TEXT>

