<H3> <TI>   Ambassador Says France Ready To Grant Security Guarantees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601220494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
2000 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601220494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine's President Leonid Kravchuk has received 
Michel-Yves Peissik, ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary of the French Republic to Ukraine. Issues on 
the further development of Ukrainian-French relations and the 
participation of the two states in the world processes were 
discussed during the conversation, which was held in an 
atmosphere of an open exchange of opinions and mutual 
understanding. The ambassador said that, in France, they highly 
assess the trilateral statement by the presidents of Ukraine, 
Russia, and the United States concerning nuclear disarmament. 
France is ready to grant security guarantees to Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

