<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Reports Progress in CFE Reduction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2601123594 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 25 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2601123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "There Will Be Much Scrap Metal"] </F>
  [Text] As reported by the Press Service of Ukraine's 
Ministry of Defense, in accordance with the agreement on 
conventional armed forces in Europe, Ukraine is further reducing 
its own weapons arsenals. During the first stage, which ended 
on 17 November 1993, 603 tanks, 630 armored combat vehicles, and 
175 aircraft and helicopters were destroyed. The second stage 
will end in November 1994. Over this period of time, it is 
planned to destroy more than 600 tanks and more than 300 armored 
combat vehicles. 
  The reduction of the numerical strength of Ukraine's Armed 
Forces is continuing. In accordance with the Supreme Council 
decision, by the end of 1995, we will have 450,000 servicemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

