<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Soviet Ousts Shushkevich as Chairman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2701085394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0800 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2701085394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Supreme Soviet of the Republic of Belarus has 
supported, by a majority of votes, the recalling of Stanislav 
Shushkevich from the post of chairman of the Supreme Soviet of 
the Republic of Belarus. The formal reason for this recall was 
the parliamentary debate which intended to reveal the violations 
of law in the activities of commercial structures at state and 
local government bodies. According to the adopted resolution, 
Shushkevich is blamed for failing to take measures against 
corruption, a lack of control over the work of law enforcement 
bodies, and manifested personal immodesty. 
  The same charges with regard to Belarusian Prime Minister 
Vyacheslav Kebich were treated by the majority of the people's 
deputies as insignificant; in secret balloting, they voted 
against his dismissal. Half an hour ago, the Supreme Soviet 
began its regular plenary session. People's deputies are 
discussing the miscellaneous matters on the agenda. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

