<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Voting Results Announced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2601201594 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1918 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2601201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of protocol on results of Supreme Soviet vote to </F>
recall Chairman Stanislav Shushkevich and Prime Minister 
Vyacheslav Kebich, announced at the evening session in Minsk by 
People's Deputy Ivan Bambiza, head of the vote-counting 
committee -- live] 
  [Text] Protocol No. 3 of the session of the vote-counting 
committee on the secret ballot vote to recall Belarusian Supreme 
Soviet Chairman Stanislav Stanislavovich Shushkevich and to 
dismiss Vyacheslav Frantsevich Kebich from the post of 
Belarusian Council of Ministers chairman, dated 26 January 1994. 
Present were: Ivan Bambiza, chairman of the vote-counting 
committee; committee secretary Nikalay Harelik; members of the 
counting committee -- Alyaksandr Belyy, Olga Lukovnich, Nikalay 
Zhuravlev, Alyaksandr Kuzmenkov, Alyaksandr Kryuchkov, Frants 
Minkov, Vitaliy Malashko, Uladzimir Novikaw, Zinaida Penkova, 
Viktar Rusak, and Viktar Fedarenka. The agenda of the session: 
On the results of the secret ballot vote to recall Belarusian 
Supreme Soviet Chairman Stanislav Stanislavovich Shushkevich and 
dismiss Vyacheslav Frantsevich Kebich from the post of 
Belarusian Council of Ministers chairman . 
  1. The vote-counting committee conducted the vote count on 
the secret ballot to recall Belarusian Supreme Soviet Chairman 
Stanislav Stanislavovich Shushkevich. 
  To conduct the vote, peoples deputies were given 290 
ballots. 
After unsealing the boxes, 250 ballots were discovered, 
including five invalid ballots. 
  The votes were distributed as follows: 
  For recalling Stanislav Stanislavovich Shushkevich from the 
post of Belarusian Supreme Soviet chairman, 209 votes were cast. 
  Against -- 36 votes. 
  2. The vote-counting committee conducted the vote count on 
the secret ballot to discharge Vyacheslav Frantsevich Kebich 
from the post of Belarusian Council of Ministers chairman. 
  To conduct the vote, peoples deputies were given 290 
ballots. 
After unsealing the boxes, 281 ballots were discovered, 
including five invalid ballots. 
  The votes were distributed as follows: 
  For discharging Vyacheslav Frantsevich Kebich from the post 
of Belarusian Supreme Council chairman, 101 votes were cast. 
  Against -- 175 votes. 
  Signatures of the committee's chairman, secretary, and 
members [appear at the bottom of the protocol]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

