<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputies To Discuss Candidates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2701122694 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1100 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2701122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The morning proceedings of the Belarusian parliament 
session have begun with miscellaneous matters on the agenda. 
The people's deputies addressed the problems of the Belarusian 
Peasant Party and the Minsk Tractor Factory, and honored the 
memory of writer Ales Adamovich by a minute of silence. Then it 
was resolved to hold necessary consultations to select 
candidates for the post of the Supreme Soviet chairman. 
However, even after a two-hour break in the proceedings, during 
which the sessions of the Supreme Soviet Presidium and 
parliamentary factions took place, the people's deputies deemed 
this issue to be unprepared for broad discussion. They decided 
to fully devote today's proceedings in commissions and deputy 
factions to the nomination of candidates for the post of the 
Supreme Soviet chairman. This issue is expected to be discussed 
at the plenary session tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

