<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich Offered Head of CIS Parliamentary Assembly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701101194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1226 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Minsk January 27 TASS -- Vladimir Shumeyko, the 
speaker of the upper chamber of the Russian parliament, offered 
Stanislav Shushkevich, who was removed from the post of the 
chairman of the Belarusian parliament on Wednesday, to head the 
CIS Interparliamentary Assembly, it was learned here from an 
anonymous sourse close to Shushkevich. 
  The offer was made on Thursday morning by telephone. This 
post was previous held by Ruslan Khasbulatov, who was jailed 
after the October opposition rebellion in Moscow. 
  Shumeyko informed Shushkevich that the offer was agreed with 
the heads of CIS parliaments. It is worth recalling in this 
connection that Shushkevich was a co-founder of the Commonwealth 
of Independent States (CIS) alongside with Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin and Ukrainian leader Leonid Kravchuk. 
  BELINFORM reported also with reference to the press service 
of the Belarus Supreme Soviet that Shushkevich would not attend 
a meeting of the Belarus parliament today. He is expected to 
hold a press conference here on Monday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

