<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sides Accuse Each Other of Launching Offensives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701120494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1057 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following a night lull, Azeri forces resumed 
offensive in the south and southeastern areas of the 
Armenian-Azeri war zone, a spokesman for the Karabakh defense 
told Interfax. As of 10:30 Moscow time, Karabakh units were 
engaged in heavy fighting, repelling the enemy attack. 
  Stepanakert reports that a pitched battle is raging in the 
north of the Kelbajar District of Azerbaijan. In a successful 
counter attack the Karabakh forces have reportedly advanced 
several kilometers on the Omar mountain pass. 
  Meanwhile, an official of the Azeri Defense Ministry told 
Interfax that fighting was underway in the Mardakert District of 
Nagorno Karabakh, where the Armenian units were still trying to 
mount a large scale offensive on the town of Ter-Ter. The town 
was shelled during the night. 
  Baku reports that the Azeri units repelled all enemy attacks 
and knocked out one enemy tank and two armored personnel 
carriers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

