<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Contradictory Reports on Fighting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601131794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1101 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2601131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Controversial reports are coming from Baku and 
Stepanakert about the fighting in the zone of the Armenian-Azeri 
conflict. 
  A spokesman for the Azeri Defence Ministry has said that 
units of the Azeri army yesterday held successful operations in 
the Kelbadzhar area of the republic. As a result, the spokesman 
said, the Kelbadzhar group of the Armenian army was forced to 
retreat to the Armenian-Azeri border, while Armenian units 
fighting in the Mardakert area of Karabakh weer being cut off 
from supply bases in Armenia. 
  Meanwhile, a spokesman for the Karabakh defense army claims 
that there are no position changes in the Kelbadzhar area. The 
spokesman said that up to 70 Azeri servicemen were killed during 
hostilities in the area. Among the Karabakh casualties are four 
persons killed and 11 wounded. 
  The spokesman said that on Wednesday morning Azeri troops 
resumed the offensive in the south-east and southern sections of 
the front. 

</TEXT>

