<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Social Democrats for Rapprochement With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601173294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1651 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2601173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi January 26 TASS -- The political council of 
the Georgian Social Democratic Party has called for 
rapprochement with Russia, "Georgia's natural great ally." 
  "This approach is the only chance for Georgia to preserve 
its 
integrity and independence," the council said in an appeal to 
Georgian leader Eduard Shevardnadze on Wednesday. 
  The Georgian leadership should admit that for various 
subjective reasons the social, economic, financial and credit 
policy of the government has failed. The severance of 
traditional ties caused by the sweeping disintegration of the 
Soviet Union has resulted in the collapse of whole industries in 
the republic, the appeal said. 
  Georgian Social Democrats disagree with the position of 
political organisations which oppose the rapprochement with 
Russia, "the only potential country whose powerful industry 
makes it a desired partner not only for us, but for more 
developed countries as well," the appeal said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

