<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Congratulates Galazov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601154594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1425 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2601154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz January 26 TASS -- "On instructions from 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin, I warmly congratulate Akhsarbek 
Galazov with his taking office of president of the Republic of 
North Ossetia. I also congratulate the people who have such a 
leader." This was stated today in Vladikavkaz by Sergey Filatov, 
head of the Russian president's administration, at a meeting of 
the Supreme Soviet of the republic devoted to assuming office by 
the first president of the republic. 
  North Ossetia, Sergey Filatov stressed, has never suffered 
from anarchy. But it is necessary to change structures of 
power, this is the call of the time. The republic has been 
confidently carrying out democratic reforms against the 
background of social and political life in Russia. 
  Some republics, the head of Russian president's 
administration said, "believe that president is needed to 
protect the republic from the central power. This is an 
erroneous position. [The] president is necessary to become a 
connecting link between the center and the republic so that all 
our Russia lived as a single family". 
  I am sure, Sergey Filatov said, that the multinational 
people 
of North Ossetia "associate their revival with strong democratic 
power in the republic. This will help successfully resolve all 
complex problems in economics, political life and in the social 
sphere. What is more, this is possible with close interaction 
between all branches of power and the observance of the 
Constitution and Russian laws". 
  According to Sergey Filatov, Boris Yeltsin asked to convey 
that he would render all-round support both to the president and 
the people of North Ossetia. 

</TEXT>

