<H3> <TI>   Khabarovsk To Hold Back Payments to Federal Budget </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701121094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1057 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In view of serious financial problems, Khabarovsk 
territory will not make any payments to the federal budget in 
January, Head of the Khabarovsk Territorial Administration 
Viktor Ishayev told Interfax. 
  He said that his territory experienced a dire energy crisis. 
Meanwhile, the federal debt to Khabarovsk territory for the 
manufactured products and for the seasonal transportation of 
loads to the northern districts of the Amur region amounts to 
billions of rubles, said Ishayev. 
  The situation is aggravated by the forced stoppage of local 
industrial enterprises which cannot make planned payments to the 
federal budget. 

