<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Brazauskas Leaves for Netherlands </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2601171594 Tallinn BNS in English 1349 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2601171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 26, BNS -- Lithuanian President 
Algirdas Brazauskas left for a one-day visit to the Netherlands 
Wednesday morning. 
  The president is accompanied by Foreign Minister Povilas 
Gylys, Defense Minister Linas Linkevicius and other officials. 
  The program of the visit includes meetings with Queen 
Beatrix, the Dutch premier and the leadership of the Dutch 
parliament. 
  Minister Gylys intends to sign a Lithuanian-Dutch agreement 
on investment protection and promotion. 
  On Thursday, the Lithuanian leader will be in Brussels, 
where 
he is scheduled to sign the Partnership for Peace framework 
document. 
  Brazauskas also intends to meet with the leadership of NATO, 
Secretary General of the European Union Willem Van Eskelen, 
Chairman of the European Commission Jacques Delors and Belgian 
Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene. 

</TEXT>

