<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier: Arrest To `Cast a Chill' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2601210694 Tallinn BNS in English 1617 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2601210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 26, BNS -- The reaction of Belarusian 
authorities to the arrest of two Lithuanian communist leaders in 
Minsk will "undoubtedly cast a chill over our relations" with 
Belarus, Lithuanian Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius said on 
Lithuanian radio Wednesday. 
  The premier said he regrets such "energetic" reaction, which 
shows that Lithuania's neighbors "have not yet completely shaken 
off old principles and formulas." In Slezevicius' opinion, the 
problem also resulted from political tensions in Belarus. 
  The Lithuanian premier said the arrest operation in Minsk 
was 
indeed very successful and fully coordinated with Belarusian 
authorities. 
  Slezevicius said he will seek to further expand the earlier 
positive developments in Lithuanian-Belarussian relations. 

</TEXT>

