<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Main Tenets of Draft Defense Doctrine Outlined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2601154994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 26 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM2601154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Valeriy Gromak report: "Lithuania's Draft Defense Doctrine </F>
Published"] 
  [Text] Vilnius -- The purpose of defense is to protect the 
independence, inviolability, and territorial integrity of 
Lithuania and also to guarantee its citizens' safety from 
external threats, the preamble to this document states. 
  In what situations can Lithuania's armed forces be used? The 
document answers this question by saying that aggression by 
another state or military alliance, civil war in neighboring 
states or an armed conflict between them which might spread to 
Lithuania, an invasion by uncontrolled military units or other 
armed groupings, a large concentration of military force near 
the Lithuanian border, or international terrorism constitute 
such situations. True, Lithuania prefers primarily political 
and diplomatic methods to eliminate threats. 
  The draft also points out that in strengthening its security 
Lithuania cooperates with other states and international 
organizations and bases itself on the universally recognized 
principles of international law. 
  The army constitutes the basis of Lithuania's defense 
system. 
  The section on cooperation with foreign states' military 
structures provides for participation in joint exercises, the 
training of joint peacekeeping subunits, and cooperation in 
guarding the state border. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

