Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 26, BNS -- The Lithuanian president 
has appointed career serviceman Stanislovas Stancikas as the 
head of the Lithuanian State Border Defense Service. 
  Colonel Stancikas, 47, held the post in 1991-1992, but was 
dismissed by then Prime Minister Gediminas Vagnorius. 
  The new chief border guard received his military education 
in 
Russia. The president's entourage characterizes him as "an 
initiative worker with a strong feeling of responsibility." 
  Stancikas replaced Petras Dragunaitis who served as the 
temporary head of the service. 

