<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Fierce Battles' in Karabakh; Losses Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2601161494 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2601161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An extremely tense situation exists at the Karabakh 
battlefronts. Fierce battles are continuing along almost all 
the front lines. 
  Nagorno-Karabakh Republic Defense Army headquarters reported 
that Azerbaijani troops resumed the offensive on the southern 
and southeastern sector of the battlefront this morning. By 
midday the Karabakh formations were still managing to halt the 
enemy's attacks. 
  A large attack is also expected on the other sectors of the 
front. This is confirmed by reconnaissance data. 
  Positional battles are continuing in the north of 
Kelbadzharskiy Rayon. According to confirmed data, 70 
Azerbaijani soldiers were killed and seven tanks were hit in 
this sector on 25 January. Four fighters were killed and 11 
were injured on the Karabakh side. 
  The Armenian Defense Ministry press service reported at 1100 
that there has been relative calm in the border regions of 
Armenia. 

</TEXT>

