<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Continues Official Visit to PRC </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hands Jiang Zemin Invitation </H4>
<F P=102> LD2801052794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0400 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801052794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS correspondents Grigoriy Arslanov, Georgiy Shmelev] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 28 Jan -- "Our visit is taking place on the 
eve of the most popular holiday in China -- Chunjie -- the 
holiday of Spring. This is a good omen for the further 
development of Chinese- Russian relations," PRC President Jiang 
Zemin stated at the Zhongnanhai party and political residence 
today during a meeting with Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev, who is here on an official visit. 
  The leader of the PRC said that he was glad about the 
meeting 
with the Russian minister and cited a Chinese proverb in this 
connection: "Meetings with old friends are a source of 
particular joy." Jiang Zemin recalled that during the visit to 
Beijing by Russian President Boris Yeltsin in December 1992, a 
conversation rich in content took place between the heads of the 
two states. 
  Andrey Kozyrev, for his part, noted that the Chinese and 
Russian new years are starting with confirmation of a course 
aimed at goodneighborliness and partnership, the foundations for 
which were laid during the visit to Beijing by Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin. Kozyrev handed to Jiang Zemin a personal message 
from Boris Yeltsin containing an invitation to make an official 
visit to the Russian Federation. 

</TEXT>

