<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Continues Official Visit to PRC </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Li Peng </H4>
<F P=102> LD2801035494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0230 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801035494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS correspondents Grigoriy Arslanov, Georgiy Shmelev] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 28 Jan -- This morning Li Peng, prime 
minister of the PRC State Council, received Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev, who is here on an official visit, at 
the Zhongnanhai party and government residence. 
  Greeting the Russian minister, Li Peng stressed that the 
visit of Russian President Boris Yeltsin to Beijing at the end 
of 1992 was an exceptionally successful one, that fruitful and 
business-like conversations on all aspects of Chinese-Russian 
relations took place. Ties between the PRC and Russia, Li Peng 
noted, are developing successfully on the basis of friendship, 
good-neighborliness and mutual advantage, in spite of the 
changes in the world and in our countries. 
  Andrey Kozyrev, in his turn, said that the purpose of his 
visit is not only to maintain the relations that currently exist 
between the two countries, but also to further expand them, to 
come out on a new, higher level of development in relations. In 
this respect, he noted, we intend to discuss the forthcoming 
visit to Moscow by PRC President Jiang Zemin and other Chinese 
leaders. 
  The Russian minister conveyed very best wishes from the 
Russian president and his words that Russia does not intend to 
back down even a single step on reform, on foreign policy, a 
priority trend in which is the development of goodneighborliness 
and partnership with China. 

</TEXT>

