<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Continues Official Visit to PRC </TI></H3>
<H4>   Holds News Conference </H4>
<F P=102> LD2801070694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0545 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801070694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Vladimir Oreshin, Pavel Spirin] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 28 Jan -- The "constructive partnership" 
which Russia is offering its eastern neighbor China implies a 
new, qualitatively higher level of contacts and ties between the 
two states. This was stated in Beijing today by Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev at a news conference for Chinese and 
foreign journalists. Replying to a question put by the 
ITAR-TASS correspondent, Kozyrev explained: "We shall not 
forget that China and Russia are two great regional powers, in 
several regions simultaneously moreover, be it central, western, 
or southeast Asia, that our regional cooperation embraces half 
the world. Moreover both countries are global powers, permanent 
members of the UN Security Council. 
  In the economy, the minister continued, saying "constructive 
partnership" presupposes a transition to higher and more stable 
forms of cooperation. First and foremost this applies to cross 
border contacts in which, in the opinion of Andrey Kozyrev, "a 
change over must be made from petty commercial deals to 
long-term joint projects." 
  Summing up the working part of his visit to the PRC, the 
Russian minister noted that in conversations with PRC chairman 
Jiang Zemin, State Council Premier Li Peng, and Foreign Minister 
Qian Qichen, a mutual striving to develop cooperation was 
confirmed, and "the strategic, long-term nature of bilateral 
mutual relations that is not subject to the vacillations of the 
state of the market, the foundations of which were laid during 
the visit of Russian President Boris Yeltsin." 
  "We have mapped out a program of mutual visits, the 
culmination of which should be a trip to Moscow by PRC Chairman 
Jiang Zemin," the Russian minister pointed out. 

</TEXT>

