<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Turnover With China Totals $7.68 Billion </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801073994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0715 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2801073994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Oreshin] </F>
  [Text] Beijing January 28 TASS -- Russian-Chinese trade is 
constantly expanding and the turnover totalled 7.68 billion US 
dollars in 1993 which is a 30 per cent increase compared to the 
previous year, according to Shi Guangsheng, Chinese deputy 
foreign trade and foreign economic cooperation minister. 
  He told a press conference on Friday [28 January] that 
Chinese exports to Russia grew by 15 per cent and amounted to 
2.69 billion dollars while Russian imports increased by 41.4 per 
cent and totalled 4.99 billion dollars. 
  Currently 27,000 Chinese are working in Russia where there 
are 2,000 joint ventures in which the share of the Chinese 
capital totals 82 million dollars, according to the deputy 
minister. 
  Georgraphic advantages and similarity in economies will 
allow 
both countries to boost equal and profitable contacts, he added. 
  Wu Yi, Chinese foreign trade and foreign economic 
cooperation 
minister, stressed that in general the Chinese foreign trade 
turnover grew 18.2 per cent in 1993 and amounted to 195.72 
billion dollars. Chinese imports went up by 29 per cent (103.95 
billion dollars) and exports by eight per cent (91.77 billion 
dollars). 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

