<H3> <TI>   PRC, ROK Concerned About Patriot Deployment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2801122394 Moscow Radio Moscow in Korean 1000 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2801122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing and Seoul are expressing concern about the 
U.S. plan to deploy the anti-missile Patriot system of the U.S. 
Forces in the ROK. 
  The United States is planning to introduce Patriot missiles 
into the ROK under the fabricated pretext [nalchodoen kusillo] 
that the DPRK has missile attack capability. 
  According to AFP reports from Seoul, ROK political circles 
are concerned about the possibility that nuclear talks with 
Pyongyang will go amiss [patan] due to the deployment of those 
missiles. 
  Beijing has officially opposed the attempt to deploy 
missiles. A spokesman for the PRC Foreign Ministry stated that 
the PRC opposes any action [imuiui haengdong] detrimental to 
peace and security of the Korean peninsula. 

</TEXT>

