<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Commander Against Fleet's `Politicization' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701235794 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2030 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701235794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sevastopol -- 27 January marks one year since 
Admiral Eduard Baltin was appointed to the post of Black Sea 
Fleet [BSF] commander. In an interview for a UNIAN 
correspondent on the occasion of this date the BSF commander 
said that he comes out against the fleet's politicization. 
According to the admiral, despite a number of agreements 
reached by the presidents of Ukraine and Russia, the status of 
the fleet remains suspended thus giving rise to problems as far 
as the material basis and the personnel are concerned. Eduard 
Baltin pointed out that the preservation of the Black Sea Fleet 
as a combat unit and an outpost on the borders of the 
Commonwealth countries are regarded by him as a priority at the 
present stage. The BSF commander is anxiously waiting for the 
heads of the two states to find a solution acceptable to both 
sides. 

</TEXT>

