<H3> <TI>   Edict Issued on Regulating Commissions, Councils </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701153094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0800 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2701153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 27 Jan -- With the coming into force of the 
Constitution of the Russian Federation and for the purposes of 
regulating the activity of commissions and councils under the 
Russian Federation president, Boris Yeltsin has signed an edict 
"On Established State Posts in Commissions and Councils Under 
the Russian Federation President". The edict establishes that 
work in commissions and councils under the Russian Federation 
president is done on a voluntary basis and does not represent 
federal state service. Established state posts in these 
commissions and councils can be introduced by decision by the 
Russian Federation president. 
  The edict comes into force on publication. 
  This was reported by the press service of the Russian 
Federation president. 

</TEXT>

