<H3> <TI>   Military Counterintelligence Group Said in Works </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK2701083094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 27 Jan 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK2701083094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Hold the Front Page!" </F>
rubric: "KGB Continues To Fragment"] 
  [Text] Information has come to MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS from 
trustworthy sources about a new reorganization of the Russian 
state security structure. 
  The president's staff is processing documents on the 
creation 
of yet another special service. Plans are in the works to 
remove the military intelligence directorate from the Russian 
Federation Federal Counterintelligence Service, and to create on 
its basis a separate state security structure. This is being 
done in order to place the military counterintelligence men in 
control of the army directly under the president of Russia. 

</TEXT>

