<H3> <TI>   Further on Navy's Protest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701131894 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0831 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701131894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sevastopol -- The Black Sea Fleet Press Center 
reports that over 20 combat ships of the Black Sea Fleet put out 
to sea on 26 January in accordance with the plan for 1994 to 
practice combat training tasks. One of the aims of the Black 
Sea Fleet sailors' training exercise is to provide instruction 
for their young reinforcements, with 4,500 conscripts from 
Ukraine among them. 
  The command of the Black Sea Fleet, in the words of Mykola 
Savchenko, Ukrainian Navy Press Center head, did not coordinate 
its actions with respect to this training exercise, either with 
the Navy commander or the Ukrainian Defense Ministry, which 
contravenes the accord between the Russian and Ukrainian 
presidents of 17 June 1993. In particular, it contravenes 
Article 6, in accordance with which the fleet command was to 
have notified not only the Ukrainian Defense Ministry and the 
president of Ukraine in advance, but also the leadership of 
Sevastopol and the Crimea. 

</TEXT>

