<H3> <TI>   Army To Increase Peacekeeping Contingent in FRY </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701173394 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1200 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2701173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] According to a decision of the Ukrainian Supreme 
Council, the Ukrainian contingent of the UN forces in the former 
Yugoslavia will be doubled in the next few months. Additional 
personnel and arms are already been sent to the Ukrainian 
battalion in Sarajevo. Despite the considerable losses 
sustained by the battalion while carrying out its peacekeeping 
mission -- six servicemen have been killed and about 30 wounded 
over a period of 18 months -- there is no shortage of 
volunteers. This is the only Ukrainian Army military unit in 
which three to four candidates are competing for each post. 
Indeed, many parents are asking commanders to send their sons 
to serve precisely in this subunit. The reason is simple: Each 
man here gets about 10 times more than the Ukrainian defense 
minister. For the first time, servicewomen have been included 
in the new personnel of the battalion. These Ukrainian Amazons 
will be able, where necessary in combat conditions, render first 
aid to their male colleagues. 

</TEXT>

