<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani SU-25 Shot Down </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2701182094 Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service in 
Armenian 1701 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2701182094 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 27 Jan (ARMENPRES)--The relative calm 
prevailing on Armenia's borders for the last few days was again 
disrupted today. The Azerbaijani Army formations shelled Sotk 
(former Zod) in Vardenisskiy Rayon with Grad rockets at 1730 
today. 
  At the same time, two SU-25 warplanes belonging to the 
Azerbaijani Air Force violated our Republic's airspace and 
dropped two bombs around Sotk. 
  Our border guards took countermeasures and silenced the 
enemy, shooting down one of the two SU-25 planes. 
  There are no casualties but there is destruction on our 
side. 

