<F P=102>  LD2801111594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1058 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2801111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Urgent" item -- By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Kuzmin] </F>
  [Text] Tehran January 28 TASS -- "Kazakhstan bears 
responsibility for its nuclear weapons itself. It does not 
intend to eliminate them or transfer them to other places until 
the non-use of such weapons is guaranteed at the world level and 
the planet gets rid of them", Ambassador of Kazakhstan in Iran 
Myrzadai Zholdasbekov said in an interview with the Iranian 
"JOMHURI-YE ESLAMI" newspaper. 
  The ambassador added that he was expressing the official 
position of Kazakhstan about which U.S. President Bill Clinton 
will be informed during President Nursultan Nazarbayev's visit 
to the United States. 
  The Kazakh Embassy in Tehran opened on January 25. 

