<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester Government Responds to Lebed Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701151894 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1757 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 26/1/1994 -- The press service 
of Dniester president and government issued today a communique 
about the recent meeting of general Aleksandr Lebed, commander 
of 14th Army, with representatives of Women's Committee in 
Tiraspol, Tighina (Bender) and Grigoriopol. The communique 
states that Lebed has called the Dniester leaders "alcoholics 
and mafiosi who sold and lost in booze-ups the Moldovan Dniester 
Republic." He said that "the direct presidential governing is 
now introduced in Dniester and the Soviets will be dissolved; as 
a consequence the Moldovan Dniester republic disappears until 
February 28th. Russia has its problems and no one will be 
concerned about Dniester as long as the present leadership is at 
power." According to the communique, Lebed also stated that 
Dniester did not need its own army and that the Dniester 
Ministry of Defence required too much armament from the 14th 
Army. 

</TEXT>

