<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks on 14th Army Withdrawal Postponed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701133094 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1757 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 26/1/1994 -- The 8th round of 
Moldovan-Russian talks on the statute, conditions and agenda of 
the 14th Army retreat, planned for the end of February in 
Chisinau has been postponed, stated to BASA Lieutenant Colonel 
Anatol Cosciug, head of Military Politics and Treaties Section 
of the Moldovan Defense Ministry. Cosciug specified that for 
the time being the parties failed to establish the day of 
beginning the talks, since presently the retreat is discussed at 
the highest level. The previous round was postponed because 
Russia demanded to grant special juridical statute to Moldova 
east regions as a condition for the Army's withdrawal. 

</TEXT>

