<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier on Growing Tension in Ties With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701202394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2009 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2701202394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladas Burbulis] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius January 27 TASS -- "I regret to say that at 
present certain tension has emerged in relations between 
Lithuania and Russia," Lithuanian Prime Minister Adolfas 
Slezevicius said. 
  Speaking about Russian-Lithuanian trade and economic 
relations at a news conference in Vilnius on Thursday, 
Slezevicius also expressed "regret that Moscow has so far failed 
to respond to our note on the enactment of the agreement on 
most-favoured nation status in trade which was signed in 
November last year during Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin's visit to Vilnius." 
  The Lithuanian premier also said that the talks on Russian 
military transit from the Kaliningrad region to Russia through 
Lithuania are moving very slowly. 

</TEXT>

