<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Fails To Agree on Response to Kozyrev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2701212494 Tallinn BNS in English 1844 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2701212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Tallinn, Jan 27, BNS -- The Estonian parliament 
today discussed the text of a statement concerning Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev's speech, which 30 legislators 
submitted on Jan. 19. 
  Kozyrev's remarks defined the Baltic states as belonging in 
Russia's sphere of influence and justified a continued illegal 
presence of Russian troops in Estonian territory. 
  Vello Saatpalu, chairman of the parliamentary Foreign 
Commission, proposed to wind up the discussion and prepare a new 
statement. Several MPs expressed their dissatisfaction with the 
parliament's standing rules under which urgent issues cannot be 
added to the agenda, and referred to the example of the 
Lithuanian parliament, which reacted to Kozyrev's speech the 
same day it was delivered. The Estonian parliament failed to 
reach a decision today because the time ran out and the 
legislators did not agree to prolong the session. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

