<H3> <TI>   Prosecution of LDPR Representative Rozhok Sought </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2701162594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 27 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM2701162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Leonid Levitskiy: "Estonia Wants To Prosecute </F>
LDPR Representative"] 
  [Text] Tallinn -- Estonian Justice Minister Kaido Kama has 
called for proceedings to be instituted against Petr Rozhok, the 
representative of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia [LDPR] 
in Estonia. 
  The minister considers his activity hostile and aimed 
against 
the Estonian state. Juri Pihl, general director of the security 
police, replied to the minister through the press. He confirmed 
that Rozhok has an LDPR party card. There are around 20 members 
of this party in Estonia. 

</TEXT>

