<H3> <TI>   Crimean Candidate Refuses Debate With Rival </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801103594 Moscow Programma Radio Odin Network in Russian 
0830 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Programma Radio Odin Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The radio and television debates between Nikolay 
Bagrov and Yuriy Meshkov, the candidates for the post of 
president of Crimea, planned for today and tomorrow will not now 
take place. In an official statement on his refusal, Yuriy 
Meshkov accused his opponent of using state media funds to 
discredit other candidates for the post of president. In 
Meshkov's opinion, this propaganda machine is now aimed at him. 
In addition there have been threats against him and his family. 
In such conditions, Yuriy Meshkov believes, it is impossible to 
take part in a discussion at the same table as Nikolay Bagrov. 

</TEXT>

