<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich Absent From Current Parliament Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801125794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1234 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2801125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk January 28 TASS -- Ousted speaker of the 
Belarusian parliament Stanislav Shushkevich is absent at the 
current session of the parliament which is to elect a new 
country's leader. 
  Sources in his close entourage said he is staying in his 
countryside residence in order "to quietly, without emotions 
consider what has happened and how to act". 
  Spokesman of the Belarusian parliament Vasiliy Vorobev 
hinted 
that Shushkevich would hardly agree to become the chairman of 
the CIS Parliamentary Assembly, the post proposed to him by 
Vladimir Shumeyko, the speaker of the Federation Council, the 
upper chamber of the Russian Parliament. 
  The post was earlier occupied by former Russian speaker 
Ruslan Khasbulatov who was arrested after the October opposition 
rebellion in Moscow. 
  Vorobev said that the statement of Shushkevich's adviser who 
said that the former leader might accept the post "reflects 
mostly the personal opinion of the adviser, rather than of 
Stanislav Shushkevich". 
  However, Vorobev said that he had not spoken with 
Shushkevich 
on the subject and added that it is too early to make any 
predictions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

