<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister, Officials View Shushkevich Ouster </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kebich: Monetary Union Not To Be Affected </H4>
<F P=102> WS2701193394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1815 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2701193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich 
gave what was probably the scantest interview of his life. 
Asked by a BELINFORM correspondent whether the dismissal of 
Stanislav Shushkevich from the office of Supreme Soviet chairman 
will affect the upcoming signing of documents on the unification 
of the Russian and Belarusian monetary systems, he simply said: 
No. 

</TEXT>

