<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister, Officials View Shushkevich Ouster </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kravchanka Affirms `Unchanged' Foreign Policy </H4>
<F P=102> WS2801085494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0800 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2801085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Petr Kravchanka has met with the 
heads of diplomatic missions in the Republic of Belarus. The 
head of the Foreign Ministry informed them of the results of the 
no-confidence vote in Stanislav Shushkevich. He also emphasized 
that the course of Belarusian foreign policy remains unchanged 
and complies with international agreements which were signed by 
Belarus, including, first of all, the agreements on nuclear 
disarmament. 

</TEXT>

