<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister, Officials View Shushkevich Ouster </TI></H3>
<H4>   Officers Union Thanks Deputies for Ouster </H4>
<F P=102> WS2801085394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0400 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2801085394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Council of the Officers' Union of Belarus has 
issued a statement thanking the people's deputies for expressing 
their nonconfidence in Shushkevich as one of the gravediggers of 
the USSR. This step is recognized by the Officers' Union as a 
beginning of the path toward condemning the Viskuli [location 
where Yeltsin, Kravchuk, and Shushkevich signed agreement to 
create CIS] plot. 

</TEXT>

