<H3> <TI>   Center Refuses To Host Yegorov, Shirkovskiy News Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2701142594 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1222 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2701142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press conference which was supposed to be held 
by Belarusian Interior Minister Vladimir Yegorov and KGB 
Chairman Eduard Shirkovskiy at 1500 [1300 GMT] on 27 January has 
been called off. As BELAPAN has learned, the management of the 
National Press Center has withheld its consent to hold the news 
conference, explaining that the ministers are just "private 
people." At the press center of the Ministry of Internal 
Affairs, a BELAPAN correspondent has learned that, in connection 
with the dismissal of [Supreme Soviet Chairman] Stanislav 
Shushkevich, Vladimir Yegorov considers the press conference 
ill-timed. Nevertheless, the Journalists' Union of Belarus is 
currently working on holding such a press conference. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

