<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commander Denies Meeting Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801102494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1000 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2801102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 28 TASS -- Commander of air-borne 
forces Yevgeniy Podkolzin refuted a report by the MOSKOVSKIY 
KOMSOMOLETS newspaper that representatives from an air-borne 
division commander participated in a secret meeting held by 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the ultra-nationalist Liberal 
Democratic Party of Russia, with the military late in December, 
reports the same newspaper on Friday. 
  It quotes Podkolzin's words that "not a single air-borne 
division or brigade commander sent his officers to this or other 
meetings". 
  Referring to an unidentified Russian intelligence officer, 
MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS wrote in the report published on Thursday 
that the LDPR leader held the meeting at a secret country house 
of the Russian Foreign Intelligence Service. 
  The report noted that the meeting was spearheaded "against 
the president and that Zhirinovskiy called on army officers to 
cooperate and pointed to the need for rapprochement between some 
parliamentary groups and commanders of combat units". 

</TEXT>

