<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Group Taking Action Over Article </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801095094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press service of Russian Union of Industrialists 
and Entrepreneurs has denied a report on a meeting between 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy and the commanders of a few army 
divisions. On 27 January, MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS published an 
article saying that a meeting took place between Zhirinovskiy 
and the commanders of several army divisions at a conspiratorial 
dacha belonging to Russia's external intelligence service, which 
was being rented by the union's leader Arkadiy Volskiy. The 
article claims that the conference was of an antipresidential 
nature. 
  In this connection, the document says, the press service of 
the Russian Union of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs believes 
it necessary to state that the information given does not 
correspond with reality and is of a provocative nature. Neither 
Volskiy nor the Russian Union of Industrialists and 
Entrepreneurs have rented or are renting any dacha belonging to 
the external intelligence service, and Zhirinovskiy has never 
been in the Union's buildings and held any conferences. The 
document also points to the serious moral and political damage 
which the publication is inflicting, both on Russia's president 
and on the union, and says that the leadership of the Union of 
Industrialists and Entrepreneurs is sending the relevant 
materials to court. 

</TEXT>

