<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Navy Protests Black Sea Fleet Exercises </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801083994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0752 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2801083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Mikhail Stetsyuk for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol January 28 TASS -- "The command of the 
Black Sea Fleet has violated agreements with the Ukrainian and 
Crimean leadership, under which it is necessary to coordinate in 
advance all movements of the personnel and armaments," the press 
centre of the Ukrainian Navy announced Thursday. 
  It circulated a statement which said that the Ukrainian 
Defence Ministry and the Ukrainian Navy had been put before the 
accomplished fact. No one had informed them in advance about 
the planned exercise. 
  The statement pointed out as well that prior to the official 
announcement of the beginning of the exercise coastal guard 
units of the Black Sea Fleet had been put on a high combat alert 
and an exercise had been held on loading the hardware on landing 
boats. 
  Such actions on the eve of presidential elections in the 
Crimea may heighten tension in the region and create conditions 
for all kinds of provocations which, of course, is 
impermissible. Since during the transitional period the Black 
Sea Fleet belongs simultaneously to the two countries, Ukraine 
and Russia, the mutual informing of the Black Sea Fleet and the 
Ukrainian Navy of the exercises, training, as well as the 
movement of personnel and armaments connected with them, is in 
line with the fraternal atmosphere, good neighbourly relations 
and the consolidation of trust and mutual understanding, the 
statement said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

