<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Fighting Shifting Toward Northern Front </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2701141294 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1300 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2701141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1300 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armenian Defense Ministry Press Service has 
reported relative calm in all the border regions of Armenia 
since last night. 
  The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic Defense Army Headquarters has 
reported that fierce battles are going on in the north of 
Kelbadzharskiy Rayon, along the Seydlar, Chatly, and Kamyshly 
line. The Azerbaijani side has sent a large force to the front 
and, despite huge losses, is still trying to break through the 
defensive line of the Karabakh fighters at any cost. The 
Karabakh side first checked the relentless pressure before 
launching a counter-attack, sending the enemy back. There are 
losses on both sides. Casualty figures are being determined. 
  The situation is also tense in Mardakertskiy Rayon, where 
fierce fighting is taking place near Tonashen. 
  Only positional exchanges of fire are occurring on the rest 
of the war fronts. 

</TEXT>

