<H3> <TI>   Vote of No Confidence in Shevardnadze Expressed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701200394 Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY in Russian 
1800 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2701200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Twelve of Georgia's political opposition parties 
have expressed a vote of no confidence in the head of state, 
Eduard Shevardnadze. They blame him for losing the war in 
Abkhazia and the total inability to rule the country. 
  The leaders of these parties also added that Eduard 
Shevardnadze should be divested of extraordinary powers 
delegated to him by the republic's parliament, which make him 
the sole ruler of the country and which, allegedly, hamper the 
opposition in participating in the "state's creative processes." 

