<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 27 Jan -- Leonid Kravchuk is most likely not 
to interfere in the affairs of Simferopol yet. Nor is he likely 
to make use of the right granted by the Supreme Council to annul 
the Crimea's legislative acts in the event they are not in 
accordance with the Ukrainian Constitution. This was a 
statement made by presidential adviser Mykola Mykhalchenko. In 
his words, there is now no formal reason for such interference. 
