<H4>   Outlines Plans for Investment Council </H4>
<F P=102> LD3001192394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1800 GMT 
30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3001192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin presented 
a proposal for a multilateral council of foreign and Russian 
bankers, investors, and entrepreneurs. He announced this at the 
world economic forum in Davos. Chernomyrdin believes this 
council could be convened this May-July in Moscow. Chernomyrdin 
thinks that Russia can use about $10-12 billion in foreign 
investments. He emphasized that conditions for foreign 
investors in Russia is gradually improving. 

</TEXT>

