<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senator Confirms Third World Sales </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR3012144193 Brussels DE MORGEN in Dutch 30 Dec 93 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> BR3012144193 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels DE MORGEN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "G.T.": "Senator Nelly Maes Confirms Massive </F>
Arms Export"] 
  [Excerpts] Brussels, 30 Dec -- "The data published 
yesterday by DE MORGEN are correct," according to Nelly Maes, VU 
[People's Union] senator. For years she has been quietly 
battling weapons exports. After comparing DE MORGEN's articles 
with her own records based on numerous parliamentary questions, 
Senator Maes claims that the data perfectly match her 
information. [passage omitted] 
  In her opinion, some blatant samples of hypocrisy are the 
delivery of mortars to Zaire on 4 December 1991, the delivery of 
guns and munition to Angola on 3 April 1991, or the export of 
808 crates of kalashnikovs to Saudi Arabia on 19 July 1991. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

