<H3> <TI>   Kohl Vows Bundeswehr To Remain Priority </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0201143294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1317 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0201143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
promised to back the Armed Forces in the dispute over the 
equipping and functions of the Bundeswehr. [passage omitted] 
Kohl announced on the private Berlin channel Hundert,6 [as 
received] today that the Bundeswehr would continue to receive 
the means necessary to fulfill its functions. While it could 
not be excepted from savings measures, its efficiency could not 
be jeopardized in the process, he said. Kohl described 
proposals to reduce further or even do away with the Bundeswehr 
as "foolish." "Those who look attentively at the world know 
that the security situation is not improving," the chancellor 
said. In this context he mentioned the events in the Balkans 
and the results gained by the Russian nationalist leader 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy in the parliamentary elections. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

