<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas Approves Coalition Cabinet List </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0101124394 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1130 GMT 1 Jan 
1994 </F>

<F P=103> TA0101124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The cabinet list formed by the Democratic Party 
[DP] and the Republican Turkish Party [RTP] was submitted to 
President Rauf Denktas today. Denktas approved of the new 
cabinet list which means that the new government has officially 
started to function. The following names appear on the cabinet 
list: Hakki Atun, prime minister; RTP leader Ozker Ozgur, state 
minister and deputy prime minister; Atay Ahmet Rasit, foreign 
affairs and defense minister; Taner Etkin, interior minister, 
Onur Borman, economy and finance minister; Mehmet Ali Talat, 
national education and culture minister; Ferdi Sabit Soyer, 
agriculture, national resource, and energy minister; Ahmet 
Kasif, public works and transportation minister; Ergin Abdullah 
Iltac, health minister; Ozkan Murat, labor and social security 
minister; Serdar Denktas, youth, sports, and environment 
minister. 
  The coalition government formed by the DP and the RTP will 
be 
submitted to the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Republican 
Assembly tomorrow. The government program, in turn, will be 
submitted to the Assembly within 10 days. 

</TEXT>

