<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin: Armenians Cannot Hold Azerbaijani Territory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA3012192793 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> TA3012192793 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] Turkey and Azerbaijan have reached an accord 
regarding the signing of a joint border protocol. 
  Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov, on an official 
visit to Turkey, held a meeting with General Dogan Gures, chief 
of the General Staff. Pointing out that there existed an 
agreement on military training between Azerbaijan and Turkey, 
Gasanov added that he will hold meetings on this issue. 
  The guest minister later departed Turkey. Seeing the guest 
minister off, Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin said that Azerbaijan 
was entering 1994 hurt and with problems. Cetin said: 
  [Begin Cetin recording] If the Armenian forces think they 
will hold on to the territories they occupied by force, they are 
wrong. We hope they will withdraw from the territories they 
have occupied. If they do not withdraw peacefully then one day 
they will have to leave those territories under other 
conditions. It is impossible that they will hold on to 
Azerbaijani territory they occupied by force in violation of all 
international regulations. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

